2026-05-03 | Position of Only Set Bit

	Question
Return position of single set bit or -1.
	Key Insight
A number has exactly one set bit if:
		n > 0 AND (n & (n - 1)) == 0  
This means it's a power of 2.
	Approach
1.	Check:
		if n == 0 → return -1  
		if (n & (n-1)) != 0 → return -1  
2.	Find position:
		count how many right shifts until n == 1  
	Time Complexity
	O(log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int findPosition(int n) {
        if(n == 0 || (n & (n - 1)) != 0)
            return -1;
        int pos = 1;
        while(n > 1){
            n >>= 1;
            pos++;
        }
        return pos;
    }
};
	Key Insight
- Power of 2 → exactly one set bit  
- Then position = number of shifts needed to reach 1  
